 \n After that, update your README file directly on GitHub if needed. \n \n \n If you create or modify the remote README file before pushing your local repository, you may run into issues. If you follow this order of steps, no problems should occur. \n\n---\n\n@vikter (2026-02-27 13:41:15Z):\n  Cloning a remote repo to a local repository  is easy, for example: \n git clone https://github.com/viktor-ter/taskman.git  \n If you want to clone and switch to a certain version of the repo this how you can do it in one line command for example: \n git clone https://github.com/viktor-ter/taskman.git . \u0026\u0026 git checkout 1e8585ae9db11347207220a6ec05c0296433e042  \n This is by the way a real repo and a real version containing the task manager level 1 tutorial application.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:39:11"},"vector":[-0.038159084,-0.0007225813,-0.022524245,0.029384753,-0.0052668788,-0.035651024,0.014046629,-0.033132765,-0.009330265,0.01952709,0.0030288983,0.02391546,-0.02812518,0.05568259,-0.026663102,-0.020022325,-0.008845033,0.016060004,0.048552226,0.009648607,-0.0030229092,-0.014401034,0.02641425,-0.0029842376,-0.009548059,0.021550475,0.004126351,-0.010791734,0.025163244,-0.003100682,0.017083187,-0.023106718,0.021017827,-0.044136897,-0.057262167,0.015607712,0.0041117608,-0.0292122,-0.03794787,0.027721897,-0.008907405,-0.014662122,0.0161086,0.0055990154,0.008983607,-0.037214074,-0.02194864,-0.009074521,-0.0005566232,-0.0063188546,-0.031775158,-0.025117857,0.03696328,-0.061517112,0.035143014,0.05991515,-0.019932525,-0.03566023,-0.014549747,-0.03775038,-0.029407807,-0.0009753979,-0.0114652,0.0023227374,0.0045150816,0.026157247,-0.027307477,-0.00391206,0.015904464,-0.058023665,0.007854249,0.019057456,-0.040174786,-0.043226615,-0.024744451,0.038741563,0.014454016,-0.015898084,0.028576255,0.0092566125,-0.016238386,0.036785953,0.00022508613,-0.02496025,-0.008314967,-0.06553232,-0.0010267858